'''Survival armor''' was a type of [[Environment suit/Legends|spacesuit]] commonly used among both large corporations and independent [[Spacer/Legends|spacers]]. Zero-G workers for the [[Tagge Mining Company]] wore survival [[Armor/Legends|armor]], and [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] kept at least one such suit aboard the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']]. The suits were equipped with a [[Jetpack/Legends|jetpack]].

==History==
[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] used Han's survival armor to infiltrate a group of Tagge workers and learn of the plans to destroy the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] fleet using the [[Omega Frost/Legends|Omega Frost]]. Luke later wore the suit when he escaped a [[Mining Explorer]] in a [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE fighter]] eventually abandoning the small craft via [[Ejector seat/Legends|ejector seat]] before it crashed into an [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroid]]. In the suit, Luke reached an asteroid where he was able to destroy a [[conductor tower]] and disable the Omega Frost.

